76561198019426640,Not Recommended,628420,35036991,Posted: 17 September,all,augustovs,"If you plan on developing a platformer, you must do two things:1) Make the controls responsive and the movement precise so that the player feels it is their fault and not the game's when they fail; and2) Use good enough art and soundtrack to not make the player want to quit after 10 minutesIf you want to sell that game, it also should be worthier of attention than any random flash game on Newgrounds or Kongregate.Somehow the developers of NGHTMN failed in all three of these tasks. They even failed to make proper menus and a tutorial showing the correct key bindings (for me it says ""jump"" is the up-key when it is actually the space bar).This is not acceptable for 99 cents. It is not acceptable for the 10 cents I paid either. If it was free I still wouldn't recommend it to anyone because it wouldn't be worth the waste of time, specially considering the literal hundreds of better platformers are available for free on Steam and on the two sites mentioned above.The developer's name is in fact a warning: everything about this is a DIGITAL MISTAKE.Ps.: Bonus negative points for the description on the top of the Steam page being a sentence apparently translated from some other language by Google Translate."
